      • create

        public ApiEntitySingleResponse create(T item)
                               throws IOException,
                                      FailedResponseException
        API call to create single T.

        Per the ThreatConnect User Documentation:

        By default, all requests that do not include an Owner are assumed to be for the API User’s Organization.
        Parameters:
        item - The type T object to create
        Returns:
        T object when it exists in ThreatConnect
        Throws:
        IOException - When the HTTPS API request fails due to IO issues
        FailedResponseException - When the API responds with an error and the request is unsuccessful
